SIMPLE: severalty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Severalty
<hw>Sev"er*al*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A state of
separation from the rest, or from all others; a holding by individual
right.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Forests which had never been owned in <qex>severalty</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Estate in severalty</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>an
estate which the tenant holds in his own right, without being joined in
interest with any other person; -- distinguished from <xex>joint
tenancy</xex>, <xex>coparcenary</xex>, and <xex>common</xex>.</cd>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Severance</ent>⟦br⟧
